        "title": "How to make an Iterator that can Iterate many types of objects",
        "body": "<p>I'm trying to make an Iterator Class that can iterate a plentitude of objects of my choice. I've seen suggestions at college about using the type Object (since it's the object superclass) but I'm not sure how to do it.<\/p>\n\n<p>I have made a constructor that receives as parameters Object[] and the number of elements. However, when I need to return that object it does not allow me saying its an incompatible type.<\/p>\n\n<pre><code>public class IteratorClass implements Iterator {\n   Object[] objIt;\n   int elemCounter;\n   int currNumber = 0;\n   /**\n   * Constructor of the Iterador\n   */\n    public IteratorClass(Object[] objIt, int elemCounter) {\n        this.elemCounter = elemCounter;\n        this.objIt = objIt;\n\n    }\n    public Object next() {\n         return objIt[currNumber++];\n    }\n<\/code><\/pre>\n\n<p>}<\/p>\n\n<p>I was expecting it to return the object of type I put in the constructor, but it's not allowing me to.<\/p>\n",
